    <!-- Church-Turing thesis -->
    <h3>The Church-Turing thesis</h3>
    <p>Every model of computation that has been proposed (lambda calculus, recursive functions, register machines, your laptop) computes exactly the same class of functions as a Turing machine. This is not a theorem but a thesis: it cannot be proved because "computable" has no prior formal definition. It has never been refuted.</p>

